Package me.dessie.dessielib.storageapi.settings

Class StorageSettings

java.lang.Object
me.dessie.dessielib.storageapi.settings.StorageSettings
public class StorageSettings extends Object
Defines the settings for a StorageContainer The following are default settings, and are applied automatically if a Container is created without modifying the settings: - Use Cache: true - Cache on Retrieve: true - Cache on Store: true - Cache Duration: 1 minute - Flush Rate: 5 minutes Some containers will change these default settings.

  • Method Details

    • setCacheDuration

      public StorageSettings setCacheDuration(int cacheDuration)
      Sets how long a cached object is cached in seconds. Note that updating this value after creating the Container will have no effect. Use as a builder call when you call the StorageSettings constructor: new StorageSettings().setCacheDuration(30)
      Parameters:
      cacheDuration - The new cache duration.
      Returns:
      The StorageSettings instance.

    • setFlushRate

      public StorageSettings setFlushRate(int flushRate)
      Sets how often the entire cache is pushed to the data structure. This value is in seconds. Set to 0 to never auto-update the cache. Note that updating this value after creating the Container will have no effect. Use as a builder call when you call the StorageSettings constructor: new StorageSettings().setFlushRate(400)
      Parameters:
      flushRate - How often, in seconds, to push the cache to the container.
      Returns:
      The StorageSettings instance.
      See Also:
      • StorageContainer.flush()

    • setUsesCache

      public StorageSettings setUsesCache(boolean usesCache)
      Sets whether the StorageContainer should cache objects. Note that disabling the cache will hinder the effectiveness of using methods such as StorageContainer.retrieve(Class, String) For example, storing an object and attempting to retrieve it right after will return null since a store is run asynchronously.
      Parameters:
      usesCache - True if objects should be cached, false if not.
      Returns:
      The StorageSettings instance.

    • setCacheOnStore

      public StorageSettings setCacheOnStore(boolean cacheOnStore)
      Sets whether objects should be cached when storing. If isUseCache() is false, this setting is ignored.
      Parameters:
      cacheOnStore - Whether the object should be cached when it's stored.
      Returns:
      The StorageSettings instance.
      See Also:
      • StorageContainer.store(String, Object)

    • getCacheDuration

      public int getCacheDuration()
      Returns how long, in seconds, a CachedObject will be cached within a StorageContainer's StorageCache. Once this timer has expired, the data will have to be retrieved from the data structure again.
      Returns:
      The cache duration

      public int getFlushRate()
      Returns how long, in seconds, the StorageContainer will update it's set cache to the data structure. Once this timer expires, the set cache is pushed and is cleared.
